1
00:00:01,991 --> 00:00:05,930
You think what you're doing right now
is called a classmate?

2
00:00:19,878 --> 00:00:23,358
[What Jae Min likes:
Music, green, beer, movie, cat]

3
00:00:31,192 --> 00:00:33,158
I don't care about debuting, too.

4
00:00:33,158 --> 00:00:34,892
Don't worry.

5
00:01:09,125 --> 00:01:13,864
Then people will get the wrong idea.

6
00:01:23,308 --> 00:01:25,163
Huh?

7
00:01:25,163 --> 00:01:26,949
A guitar.

8
00:01:27,826 --> 00:01:30,214
Hey, what's up?

9
00:01:47,365 --> 00:01:51,570
♪ Are you thinking ♪

10
00:01:51,570 --> 00:01:53,738
♪ thinking of me right now? ♪

11
00:01:53,738 --> 00:01:59,525
♪ Even in the smallest moments ♪

12
00:01:59,525 --> 00:02:02,892
♪ All I see is you ♪

13
00:02:02,892 --> 00:02:07,659
♪ Let me walk with you in a dream ♪

14
00:02:07,659 --> 00:02:11,058
♪ Till the night is gone ♪

15
00:02:11,058 --> 00:02:15,926
♪ To some place I don't know ♪

16
00:02:15,926 --> 00:02:18,162
♪ I want to run to you ♪

17
00:02:18,162 --> 00:02:22,400
♪ And fall into your arms ♪

18
00:02:22,400 --> 00:02:26,538
♪ I can't breathe, I miss you ♪

19
00:02:26,538 --> 00:02:32,538
♪ Let me show you who I am ♪

20
00:02:48,892 --> 00:02:53,063
[What Jae Min likes:
Music, green, beer, movie, cat]

21
00:02:56,392 --> 00:02:59,991
It's us!

22
00:02:59,991 --> 00:03:02,207
Nice.

23
00:03:02,207 --> 00:03:06,745
[Kim Hyun Jae, Yoon Soo An, Riki,
Lee Do Yun, Shin Jae Min, Ha Jun]

24
00:03:26,218 --> 00:03:27,966
Shin Jae Min!

25
00:03:27,966 --> 00:03:29,459
We're in the debut group together.

26
00:03:29,459 --> 00:03:30,598
Let's do this.

27
00:03:30,598 --> 00:03:31,670
Hey.

28
00:03:31,670 --> 00:03:33,378
You slacked off in practice.

29
00:03:33,378 --> 00:03:35,674
What changed?

30
00:03:35,674 --> 00:03:37,842
I wanted to sing.

31
00:03:38,625 --> 00:03:42,358
Please!

32
00:03:42,358 --> 00:03:45,149
I made it!

33
00:03:46,425 --> 00:03:47,886
Told you you'd get in.

34
00:03:47,886 --> 00:03:50,292
- Let's work hard.
- Yeah.

35
00:03:50,292 --> 00:03:52,556
- You made it.
- You made it.

36
00:03:57,258 --> 00:04:00,131
- You're here.
- Hello.

37
00:04:01,091 --> 00:04:04,625
It's tight in here with this many people.

38
00:04:04,625 --> 00:04:06,570
Sit.

39
00:04:07,985 --> 00:04:09,705
So, how does it feel?

40
00:04:09,705 --> 00:04:11,225
Being in the debut group.

41
00:04:11,225 --> 00:04:13,277
- Thank you.
- Thank you.

42
00:04:13,945 --> 00:04:17,826
I called you in to tell you each
why you got picked.

43
00:04:17,826 --> 00:04:21,311
It makes a difference, hearing the reason.

44
00:04:21,311 --> 00:04:24,753
When things get hard, think back to the reason.

45
00:04:24,753 --> 00:04:26,992
It'll help a little.

46
00:04:26,992 --> 00:04:28,091
Hyun Jae.

47
00:04:28,091 --> 00:04:29,249
You know yours.

48
00:04:29,249 --> 00:04:30,495
Do I have to spell it out?

49
00:04:30,495 --> 00:04:31,525
Please do.

50
00:04:31,525 --> 00:04:35,400
This kid's getting cocky.

51
00:04:35,400 --> 00:04:37,302
Cut him.

52
00:04:37,302 --> 00:04:39,170
You can leave.

53
00:04:40,892 --> 00:04:42,225
Let's see.

54
00:04:42,225 --> 00:04:44,437
You, the dancing.

55
00:04:44,437 --> 00:04:46,610
- He can dance.
- Thank you.

56
00:04:47,492 --> 00:04:49,037
You, the rapping.

57
00:04:49,037 --> 00:04:50,848
Thank you.

58
00:04:51,516 --> 00:04:53,759
You, you've got that variety show charm.

59
00:04:53,759 --> 00:04:55,719
Thank you.

60
00:04:57,222 --> 00:04:59,090
You?

61
00:04:59,090 --> 00:05:00,870
The eyes.

62
00:05:00,870 --> 00:05:02,760
Thank you.

63
00:05:08,759 --> 00:05:11,069
You.

64
00:05:11,069 --> 00:05:13,103
You...

65
00:05:14,940 --> 00:05:16,374
You belong here.

66
00:05:16,374 --> 00:05:18,311
The voice.

67
00:05:20,311 --> 00:05:22,581
I'm the one who picked you.

68
00:05:22,581 --> 00:05:24,882
Thank you.

69
00:05:25,592 --> 00:05:27,886
Congratulations again, all of you.

70
00:05:27,886 --> 00:05:30,914
Work hard.

71
00:05:30,914 --> 00:05:32,207
You all know this.

72
00:05:32,207 --> 00:05:35,772
Making the debut team
doesn't guarantee a debut.

73
00:05:35,772 --> 00:05:37,328
Could be all of you.

74
00:05:37,328 --> 00:05:38,692
Could be none.

75
00:05:38,692 --> 00:05:42,167
But for this team,
we're aiming for the second half of the year.

76
00:05:42,167 --> 00:05:44,261
We move fast.

77
00:05:44,261 --> 00:05:46,705
Any questions?

78
00:05:49,592 --> 00:05:51,093
Khun!

79
00:05:51,093 --> 00:05:53,378
You made it.

80
00:05:53,378 --> 00:05:54,653
Everyone met him?

81
00:05:54,653 --> 00:05:56,186
This is Khun.

82
00:05:56,186 --> 00:06:00,146
He's writing and composing the debut track.

83
00:06:00,146 --> 00:06:02,119
Pleasure to meet you all.

84
00:06:02,991 --> 00:06:04,426
Right.

85
00:06:04,426 --> 00:06:06,892
Dinner's on me tonight.

86
00:06:06,892 --> 00:06:08,692
Round of applause.

87
00:06:14,065 --> 00:06:16,225
Everyone enjoying the food?

88
00:06:16,225 --> 00:06:18,626
Sit.

89
00:06:18,626 --> 00:06:21,298
Mix it up a little, would you?

90
00:06:21,298 --> 00:06:25,042
Get to know each other.
Force it if you have to.

91
00:06:34,025 --> 00:06:35,136
Khun.

92
00:06:35,136 --> 00:06:36,820
Come here.

93
00:06:42,792 --> 00:06:44,459
Alright.

94
00:06:44,459 --> 00:06:45,904
Here.

95
00:06:51,158 --> 00:06:53,205
- Hey.
- What?

96
00:06:53,205 --> 00:06:55,046
Something's on your face.

97
00:06:55,707 --> 00:06:57,108
Where?

98
00:06:57,108 --> 00:06:58,909
No...

99
00:06:59,878 --> 00:07:01,579
Here.

100
00:07:03,492 --> 00:07:05,003
Jerk.

101
00:07:06,192 --> 00:07:08,286
Already drunk?

102
00:07:08,286 --> 00:07:09,988
Everyone got a glass?

103
00:07:09,988 --> 00:07:11,098
- Yes.
- Yes.

104
00:07:11,098 --> 00:07:13,091
No toasts these days, huh?

105
00:07:13,091 --> 00:07:14,907
Let's just say cheers. Cheers!

106
00:07:14,907 --> 00:07:17,027
- Cheers!
- Cheers!

107
00:07:18,392 --> 00:07:21,659
I'm exhausted. I'm heading out.

108
00:07:21,659 --> 00:07:23,192
- You're leaving?
- Yeah.

109
00:07:23,192 --> 00:07:25,525
Time to go.

110
00:07:25,525 --> 00:07:27,705
Eat up.

111
00:07:31,609 --> 00:07:34,148
I'm leaving this with you.
Order whatever you want.

112
00:07:34,148 --> 00:07:36,648
Get more. Go on, order more.

113
00:07:36,648 --> 00:07:38,826
- Here.
- Thank you, sir.

114
00:07:38,826 --> 00:07:39,887
All right!

115
00:07:39,887 --> 00:07:42,128
I'm really leaving now.

116
00:07:42,128 --> 00:07:43,991
Keep eating, Hyun Jae.

117
00:07:43,991 --> 00:07:46,192
Khun, come here.

118
00:07:46,192 --> 00:07:48,308
Need to talk to you.

119
00:07:48,308 --> 00:07:50,128
Come on.

120
00:07:51,225 --> 00:07:54,131
- Get home safe.
- Good night.

121
00:07:55,325 --> 00:07:57,468
He'll be back in two hours.

122
00:08:00,459 --> 00:08:02,073
Hey.

123
00:08:02,073 --> 00:08:05,897
Send the Unicorn guys and the Thai guy home,
let's just drink among ourselves.

124
00:08:05,897 --> 00:08:07,012
Why?

125
00:08:07,012 --> 00:08:08,747
We're one team now.

126
00:08:08,747 --> 00:08:10,128
One team, my foot.

127
00:08:10,128 --> 00:08:12,383
Nothing's been decided.

128
00:08:13,938 --> 00:08:15,208
You want us to leave?

129
00:08:15,208 --> 00:08:16,859
What?

130
00:08:16,859 --> 00:08:19,289
I said, you want us to leave?

131
00:08:19,948 --> 00:08:21,392
Does all of Unicorn have to leave?

132
00:08:21,392 --> 00:08:23,928
Soo An and I can just step aside.

133
00:08:23,928 --> 00:08:25,568
What's your problem?

134
00:08:25,568 --> 00:08:26,629
That's not what I meant.

135
00:08:26,629 --> 00:08:28,466
Really?

136
00:08:28,466 --> 00:08:30,634
What's with him? Guilty conscience?

137
00:08:30,634 --> 00:08:32,209
Guilty? Hey.

138
00:08:32,209 --> 00:08:34,325
- Hey.
- Easy.

139
00:08:34,325 --> 00:08:35,507
What is wrong with everyone?

140
00:08:35,507 --> 00:08:36,991
Don't do this.

141
00:08:36,991 --> 00:08:39,367
We're all drunk. Okay?

142
00:08:39,367 --> 00:08:41,438
Honestly,

143
00:08:41,438 --> 00:08:42,814
because of them,

144
00:08:42,814 --> 00:08:47,559
guys who have been training since elementary,
middle school, got cut. That's the truth.

145
00:08:47,559 --> 00:08:52,557
Our debut team was practically set.

146
00:08:52,557 --> 00:08:58,108
Then suddenly there's a merger,
and these guys show up out of nowhere.

147
00:08:58,108 --> 00:08:59,648
What about Hyuk Chan?

148
00:08:59,648 --> 00:09:01,221
Ha Neul?

149
00:09:01,221 --> 00:09:04,068
They got cut
because of these guys, didn't they?

150
00:09:04,068 --> 00:09:06,881
And what's with the guy from Thailand?

151
00:09:06,881 --> 00:09:08,822
Is he with us or not?

152
00:09:08,822 --> 00:09:10,759
Hey!

153
00:09:10,759 --> 00:09:12,302
You can't talk like that.

154
00:09:12,302 --> 00:09:13,558
What?

155
00:09:13,558 --> 00:09:15,760
Am I wrong?

156
00:09:17,792 --> 00:09:20,542
I know it's uncomfortable,

157
00:09:20,542 --> 00:09:23,161
but Ha Jun and I, we'll work hard with you.

158
00:09:23,161 --> 00:09:24,167
We trained

159
00:09:24,167 --> 00:09:26,826
- a long time at our old company too...
- Soo An.

160
00:09:26,826 --> 00:09:30,861
Are you really bowing down to these pricks?

161
00:09:30,861 --> 00:09:32,321
Ha Jun.

162
00:09:32,321 --> 00:09:36,341
If Unicorn hadn't fallen apart,
we'd have debuted way bigger.

163
00:09:36,341 --> 00:09:39,317
Then go back to Unicorn.

164
00:09:41,091 --> 00:09:42,480
He's drunk.

165
00:09:42,480 --> 00:09:44,780
That's a free pass, right?

166
00:09:44,780 --> 00:09:47,459
You think any of this is wrong?

167
00:09:47,459 --> 00:09:51,381
He's just saying
what you've all been thinking, right?

168
00:09:51,381 --> 00:09:52,939
Stop.

169
00:09:54,052 --> 00:09:55,319
He's drunk too.

170
00:09:55,319 --> 00:09:57,722
Call it even.

171
00:09:57,722 --> 00:10:00,559
Stop playing the nice guy.

172
00:10:00,559 --> 00:10:03,021
Ha Jun, let's go home.

173
00:10:04,258 --> 00:10:05,372
Let's go.

174
00:10:05,372 --> 00:10:07,292
Let's just get out of here.

175
00:10:07,292 --> 00:10:09,801
Okay.

176
00:10:09,801 --> 00:10:12,069
Let's go.

177
00:10:24,149 --> 00:10:26,049
Where are you headed?

178
00:10:27,718 --> 00:10:30,325
It's fine, I'll grab a cab.

179
00:10:30,325 --> 00:10:32,257
I'm asking where.

180
00:10:32,257 --> 00:10:33,558
I'll go with you,

181
00:10:33,558 --> 00:10:35,859
- you're pretty drunk, too...
- I'm fine.

182
00:10:37,292 --> 00:10:39,396
Don't talk down to me.

183
00:10:50,692 --> 00:10:52,091
Huh?

184
00:10:52,091 --> 00:10:53,725
Hey.

185
00:10:56,966 --> 00:10:59,546
I'll get him home.

186
00:10:59,546 --> 00:11:01,991
You go home. You look exhausted.

187
00:11:01,991 --> 00:11:03,247
Kim Hyun Jae.

188
00:11:03,247 --> 00:11:05,206
Don't talk down to me.

189
00:11:05,206 --> 00:11:07,172
Is he getting in or not?

190
00:11:07,172 --> 00:11:10,060
He's not. Just go.

191
00:11:23,025 --> 00:11:25,970
Shin Jae Min pisses me off too.

192
00:11:26,686 --> 00:11:29,192
- What?
- I'm wrong?

193
00:11:29,192 --> 00:11:30,792
You know I'm right.

194
00:11:30,792 --> 00:11:32,704
Shin Jae Min, that's his name.

195
00:11:32,704 --> 00:11:34,723
Stop it.

196
00:11:34,723 --> 00:11:37,091
You don't feel the same?

197
00:11:37,091 --> 00:11:39,925
Honestly, people only keep quiet
because of Hyun Jae.

198
00:11:39,925 --> 00:11:42,063
Who here actually likes him?

199
00:11:42,063 --> 00:11:43,373
The press is going to drag him anyway,

200
00:11:43,373 --> 00:11:45,763
and I don't get why the company
keeps covering for him,

201
00:11:45,763 --> 00:11:48,566
and our kids who got cut
because of that, damn it...

202
00:11:48,566 --> 00:11:50,644
Who's supposed to comfort them?

203
00:11:50,644 --> 00:11:54,972
Even now he's out here defending
some Thai guy who just rolled in,

204
00:11:54,972 --> 00:11:56,407
or what,

205
00:11:56,407 --> 00:11:58,260
is Shin Jae Min into him?

206
00:11:58,260 --> 00:12:01,579
Say what you want about me

207
00:12:01,579 --> 00:12:04,215
but leave Khun out of it.

208
00:12:04,215 --> 00:12:07,340
What? Something's actually going on
between you two?

209
00:12:07,340 --> 00:12:09,492
The scandal machine strikes again.

210
00:12:09,492 --> 00:12:11,300
Mad respect.

211
00:12:11,300 --> 00:12:15,958
This time a scandal with a Thai star,
the headlines are going to eat this up.

212
00:12:15,958 --> 00:12:18,559
Riki, that's enough.

213
00:12:18,559 --> 00:12:20,280
Let go.

214
00:12:20,280 --> 00:12:21,833
You want one?

215
00:12:21,833 --> 00:12:23,405
What?

216
00:12:27,405 --> 00:12:29,192
I'm asking if you want one.

217
00:12:29,192 --> 00:12:30,941
A scandal.

218
00:12:31,976 --> 00:12:34,252
The hell are you saying?

219
00:12:36,281 --> 00:12:38,158
Should we try dating then?

220
00:12:38,158 --> 00:12:39,917
Seriously.

221
00:12:44,355 --> 00:12:46,392
Hey.

222
00:12:46,392 --> 00:12:48,058
What's his deal?

223
00:12:48,058 --> 00:12:50,494
What the hell, damn it!

224
00:13:17,022 --> 00:13:18,755
Should we head out?

225
00:13:43,730 --> 00:13:45,450
You used me to get ahead and I did the same,

226
00:13:45,450 --> 00:13:47,958
and you already made your debut,
so isn't that enough?

227
00:13:47,958 --> 00:13:49,725
What?

228
00:13:49,725 --> 00:13:51,088
Just stay like this for a second.

229
00:13:51,088 --> 00:13:52,990
What's with these two?

230
00:13:53,592 --> 00:13:55,761
Do you think so, too?

231
00:13:55,761 --> 00:13:57,559
Don't let it get to you.

232
00:13:57,559 --> 00:13:59,529
See you tomorrow in class.

233
00:14:00,364 --> 00:14:02,065
You're coming, right?

234
00:14:02,733 --> 00:14:04,659
What do you want to do,

235
00:14:04,659 --> 00:14:06,958
Yoon Soo An?

236
00:14:06,958 --> 00:14:09,473
Did you see this?
